  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka bonds flat, rupee guidance peg weaker",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka\u2019s bond and Treasury bill yields were mostly flat in mid-morning trade Thursday while a guidance peg on interbank spot trading was weakened, dealers said as the country was mired in political turmoil and awaited the resignation of President Gotabaya Rajapaksa.",
        "In bond markets the the three months\u2019 bill was quoted at 32.75/33.25 percent on Thursday steady from 32.75/33 percent on July 12.",
        "A bond maturing on 01.06.25 was quoted at 28.00/29.00 percent steady from 27.00/29.00 percent in previous close.",
        "A bond maturing on 15.07.29 was quoted at 29.00/30.25 percent steady from 30.00/25 percent in previous close.",
        "A guidance peg announced by Sri Lanka\u2019s central bank for interbank transactions weakened by one rupee to 361.90 against the US dollar on July 14 from the previous 360.90, data showed on Thursday.",
        "Commercial banks offered dollars for telegraphic transfers at rates between 368.90 and 370.00 for small transactions on July 14, steady from Tuesday, online data showed.",
        "Banks offered to buy inward remittances at 358.90 -360.00 rupees, also steady from the previous day. (Colombo/July 14/2022)"
      ],
